{
  "id": "fr_a1_lesson_002",
  "language": "fr",
  "level": "A1",
  "title": "Se présenter : qui êtes-vous ?",
  "description": "Say your name, age, and nationality, count from 0 to 20, and handle the exact questions that open a real TEF/TCF oral interview.",
  "metadata": { "estimatedMinutes": 9, "xpReward": 50 },
  "cards": [
    {
      "id": "c1",
      "type": "TextCard",
      "title": "Qui êtes-vous ?",
      "content": {
        "subtitle": "Lesson 2 · A1",
        "body": "Now that you can say hello, let's learn how to introduce yourself properly: your name, your age, and where you're from. These are the very first questions asked in a real TEF/TCF interview!"
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 20 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c2",
      "type": "GrammarCard",
      "title": "Le verbe \"s'appeler\" (to be called)",
      "content": {
        "explanation": "\"S'appeler\" is a reflexive verb — the action reflects back on the subject, like saying \"I call myself...\". It's the standard way to give your name in French.",
        "examples": [
          { "text": "Je m'appelle", "translation": "My name is (lit. I call myself)" },
          { "text": "Tu t'appelles", "translation": "Your name is (informal)" },
          { "text": "Il/Elle s'appelle", "translation": "His/Her name is" },
          { "text": "Nous nous appelons", "translation": "Our names are / We are called" },
          { "text": "Vous vous appelez", "translation": "Your name is (formal/plural)" },
          { "text": "Ils/Elles s'appellent", "translation": "Their names are" }
        ]
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 40 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c3",
      "type": "VocabularyCard",
      "content": {
        "word": "Je m'appelle",
        "nativeTranslation": "Je m'appelle",
        "englishTranslation": "My name is...",
        "pronunciation": "zhuh mah-PELL",
        "ipa": "ʒə mapɛl",
        "partOfSpeech": "verb phrase",
        "difficulty": "easy",
        "exampleSentence": "Je m'appelle Sophie, et toi ?",
        "nativeExample": "My name is Sophie, and you?",
        "audio": { "key": "fr/a1/je-mappelle.mp3" }
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 30 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c4",
      "type": "VocabularyCard",
      "content": {
        "word": "J'ai ... ans",
        "nativeTranslation": "J'ai ... ans",
        "englishTranslation": "I am ... years old",
        "pronunciation": "zhay ... ahn",
        "ipa": "ʒe … ɑ̃",
        "partOfSpeech": "verb phrase",
        "difficulty": "easy",
        "exampleSentence": "J'ai vingt ans.",
        "nativeExample": "I am twenty years old.",
        "audio": { "key": "fr/a1/jai-ans.mp3" }
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 30 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c5",
      "type": "VocabularyCard",
      "content": {
        "word": "Je suis français(e)",
        "nativeTranslation": "Je suis français(e)",
        "englishTranslation": "I am French",
        "pronunciation": "zhuh swee frahn-SEZ",
        "ipa": "ʒə sɥi fʁɑ̃sɛ(z)",
        "partOfSpeech": "adjective",
        "difficulty": "easy",
        "exampleSentence": "Je suis française. Et vous, vous êtes d'où ?",
        "nativeExample": "I am French. And you, where are you from?",
        "audio": { "key": "fr/a1/je-suis-francais.mp3" }
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 30 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c6",
      "type": "InfoCard",
      "title": "Un vrai début d'entretien TEF/TCF",
      "content": {
        "tone": "tip",
        "body": "The real TEF/TCF oral exam almost always opens with exactly these three questions: \"Comment vous appelez-vous ?\", \"Quel âge avez-vous ?\", and \"D'où venez-vous ?\". Master these answers and you'll walk into the real interview with confidence."
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 25 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c7",
      "type": "GrammarCard",
      "title": "\"Tu\" ou \"vous\" pour se présenter ?",
      "content": {
        "explanation": "In an exam, an interview, or with a stranger, always use \"vous\" — it's the safe, respectful default. Save \"tu\" for friends, classmates, and people your own age in casual settings.",
        "examples": [
          { "text": "Comment vous appelez-vous ?", "translation": "What is your name? (formal — use in exams/interviews)" },
          { "text": "Comment tu t'appelles ?", "translation": "What's your name? (informal — use with friends)" }
        ]
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 35 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c8",
      "type": "FlashCard",
      "title": "Quick flip",
      "content": {
        "front": "D'où venez-vous ?",
        "back": "Where are you from? (formal)",
        "hint": "Tap to reveal the meaning"
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 15 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c9",
      "type": "GrammarCard",
      "title": "Les nombres de 0 à 20",
      "content": {
        "explanation": "Numbers 0–20 are essential for giving your age, phone number, and address — all standard TEF/TCF A1 topics. Notice 17, 18, and 19 are built from \"ten\" + the unit (dix-sept = ten-seven).",
        "examples": [
          { "text": "zéro", "translation": "0" },
          { "text": "un", "translation": "1" },
          { "text": "deux", "translation": "2" },
          { "text": "trois", "translation": "3" },
          { "text": "quatre", "translation": "4" },
          { "text": "cinq", "translation": "5" },
          { "text": "six", "translation": "6" },
          { "text": "sept", "translation": "7" },
          { "text": "huit", "translation": "8" },
          { "text": "neuf", "translation": "9" },
          { "text": "dix", "translation": "10" },
          { "text": "onze", "translation": "11" },
          { "text": "douze", "translation": "12" },
          { "text": "treize", "translation": "13" },
          { "text": "quatorze", "translation": "14" },
          { "text": "quinze", "translation": "15" },
          { "text": "seize", "translation": "16" },
          { "text": "dix-sept", "translation": "17" },
          { "text": "dix-huit", "translation": "18" },
          { "text": "dix-neuf", "translation": "19" },
          { "text": "vingt", "translation": "20" }
        ]
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 45 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c10",
      "type": "MultipleChoiceCard",
      "title": "Choisissez le bon nombre",
      "content": {
        "prompt": "Comment dit-on \"15\" en français ?",
        "options": [
          { "id": "a", "text": "cinq" },
          { "id": "b", "text": "cinquante" },
          { "id": "c", "text": "quinze" },
          { "id": "d", "text": "quatorze" }
        ]
      },
      "validation": { "correctOptionId": "c" },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 20 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c11",
      "type": "ListeningCard",
      "title": "Écoutez bien",
